Dialogue: 0,0:00:13.42,0:00:21.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.22,0:00:26.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The members of CP9 have\Nfinally made themselves known.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.60,0:00:30.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Lucci, Kaku, Blueno and Kalifa.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.60,0:00:34.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy and Zoro stood up to them\Nto put a stop to their scheme.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.27,0:00:39.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,However, Lucci, who has Cat-Cat\Nfruit powers, crushed them.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:39.69,0:00:42.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,CP9 has found out that Franky is Cutty Flam
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.78,0:00:46.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and has the blueprints for\Nthe ancient weapon Pluton.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.20,0:00:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've got nothing I could give you jerks!
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.71,0:01:02.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And they caught Franky,\Nwho challenged them, in the blink of an eye.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:02.09,0:01:05.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Man, that was rough.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.93,0:01:08.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll pay him back two times over.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.39,0:01:13.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not until we get what we want,\Nshipwright Cutty Flam.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.56,0:01:21.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The blueprints are not here!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.28,0:01:31.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay back!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.67,0:01:44.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where am I?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:44.22,0:01:46.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.18,0:01:49.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why the hell is this happening?
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.10,0:01:57.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! I'd better hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.52,0:02:07.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay! Just as I planned.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.84,0:02:23.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We were taken in by the Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:23.72,0:02:26.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're gonna make us the culprits\Nfor attacking the Judicial Ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.84,0:02:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because they want to question Tom-san\Nas a criminal to obtain the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.64,0:02:37.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,After all this... can you still\Nsay that you're innocent?!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.56,0:02:42.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If we can't somehow stop them\Nfrom taking Tom-san away...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:42.11,0:02:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'll never...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.94,0:02:51.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...forgive you for the rest of my life, Franky!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:52.08,0:02:53.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never--
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.37,0:02:54.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.83,0:02:56.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:56.12,0:02:59.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame him, Iceberg.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.54,0:03:02.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not Franky's fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:02.05,0:03:05.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're still saying that, even at this point?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.05,0:03:07.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.76,0:03:10.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm sorry! I made this harpoon!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:10.39,0:03:14.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I made it so that it can't come\Nout once it pierces its target!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.64,0:03:16.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:16.85,0:03:21.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't apologize. This is nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.02,0:03:22.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look! They're over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.86,0:03:24.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom is on the ground!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.40,0:03:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Why is he seriously injured like that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.11,0:03:29.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then, it wasn't them who made the raid?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:29.91,0:03:34.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The townspeople are here.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:34.99,0:03:36.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, then...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.75,0:03:39.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...shall we head to the town, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.67,0:03:41.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastard, Spanda!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.29,0:03:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's "Spandam"...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:44.42,0:03:50.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you criminals...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.80,0:03:55.12,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.14,0:03:58.62,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.64,0:04:01.96,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,As power passes through our clasped hands
Dialogue: 0,0:04:01.98,0:04:09.98,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:04:12.95,0:04:20.65,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Working together, let's ride the giant waves
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.67,0:04:28.03,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Let's hurry toward the excitement--\Nthere's the starting signal
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.05,0:04:34.91,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Now's the time to set sail-- let's raise anchor
Dialogue: 0,0:04:34.93,0:04:42.04,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Cut through the rainbow-colored wind\Nand head for a sea of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.06,0:04:45.42,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It'll be a journey fraught with injury
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.44,0:04:49.38,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,but what you cherish most will be right there
Dialogue: 0,0:04:49.40,0:04:53.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,And if you get into a jam
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.45,0:04:56.43,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll always be there to protect you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.45,0:05:00.60,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right! Now let's move forward
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.62,0:05:04.19,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,with the sun always in our hearts
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.21,0:05:07.15,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If a storm hits, let's put\Nour arms around each other
Dialogue: 0,0:05:07.17,0:05:11.49,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,and gaze at the light beyond
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.51,0:05:15.41,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If we gather up the pieces of our dreams
Dialogue: 0,0:05:15.43,0:05:18.66,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,they'll make a map leading to tomorrow
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.68,0:05:21.62,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,So let's grab hold of our wishes
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.64,0:05:27.42,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,under the same flag-- together, we're one
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.44,0:05:35.44,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,One Piece
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.08,0:05:45.08,B1,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(2000,2000)}"The End of the Legendary Man!\NThe Day the Sea Train Cried"
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.21,0:05:50.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,These are the raid culprits.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:50.55,0:05:52.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please rest easy, everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.63,0:05:57.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We, CP5, brought them down\Nafter they made the raid.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.05,0:05:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They can't cause any more trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:59.47,0:06:02.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He would've been found\Nnot guilty in today's trial...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.56,0:06:04.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, why did Tom do something like that?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.73,0:06:08.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So he was a friend of the\NKing of the Pirates after all, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:08.44,0:06:10.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Pleased to meet you.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.78,0:06:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm Spandam from CP5.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.40,0:06:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You happened to be there?\NThank you. You saved us.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.11,0:06:24.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please hand them over to us,\Nas we would like to investigate them.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.21,0:06:27.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Try making excuses if you like.\NOur trustworthiness is worlds apart.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.88,0:06:32.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll get the blueprints of the ancient weapon.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.38,0:06:38.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ribbit, ribbit.\N--How terrible...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:38.85,0:06:42.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,First, about the sea train,\Nall I can say is, splendid.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.60,0:06:47.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can see it'll contribute greatly\Nto the growth of Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.27,0:06:52.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For that, on the previous charge\Nfor building Gold Roger's ship,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:52.44,0:06:57.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your acquittal today had\Npretty much been decided.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.53,0:06:58.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So then, why did you commit another crime?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.95,0:07:00.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's a load of crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.41,0:07:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're not the ones who\Nraided the Judicial Ship!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.16,0:07:09.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was that Spandam guy who did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.67,0:07:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.46,0:07:14.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No way!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.21,0:07:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's got into that disciple of Tom's,\Nsuddenly cracking jokes?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.84,0:07:23.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What would CP5, a Government entity,\Ngain by sinking a Judicial Ship?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:23.97,0:07:28.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a stupid thing to say!\NThat's not possible at all!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.90,0:07:31.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Cutty Flam, was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.48,0:07:37.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To start with, we caught you\Nred-handed on one of the raid ships.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.03,0:07:45.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In addition, weren't those raid\Nships built by your company?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.25,0:07:53.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ships that would do something like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.79,0:07:57.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They're... no longer...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.38,0:08:05.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...my ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.81,0:08:11.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom tore his handcuffs apart!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:11.52,0:08:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.11,0:08:20.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san... hit Franky for the first time...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.66,0:08:24.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What'd you do that for?!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:24.83,0:08:28.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"They're no longer my ships," you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:28.29,0:08:31.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can say anything but that!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:31.08,0:08:35.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What's wrong with saying that?!\NI'm regretting it!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.71,0:08:40.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If only those ships didn't exist,\Nno one would have had to get hurt!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.80,0:08:47.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what kind of ship it is,\Nthe act of building it...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:47.06,0:08:50.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...is neither an act of good nor evil!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.77,0:08:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't care what kind of\Nships you choose to build,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.61,0:08:58.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but even if the ships you built hurt someone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.57,0:09:00.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or even if they destroy the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.86,0:09:05.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,at least the one who created\Nthem must love them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.24,0:09:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Their creator mustn't deny them!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.58,0:09:10.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't blame the ships!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.29,0:09:18.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A man should be resolutely proud...\Nof the ships he created!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.02,0:09:36.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.06,0:09:38.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Franky...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.02,0:09:41.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't interfere in what I'm about to do...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.15,0:09:44.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:44.61,0:09:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's the World Government\Nwho pinned the crime on us.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:47.58,0:09:49.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's also the World Government who judges it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.83,0:09:53.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There's no way that we'll\Nget cleared of suspicion.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.04,0:09:55.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is it.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.79,0:10:01.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be really tough for you to see\Nyour innocent ships being used like this.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.09,0:10:09.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must want to beat up\Nthat guy, right, Franky?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.31,0:10:15.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.81,0:10:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom started going on a rampage!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.94,0:10:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ribbit!\N--Oh, my God...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.82,0:10:23.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please stop! If you lay\None more finger on him...!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.74,0:10:26.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.61,0:10:29.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...understand the pain he's feeling?!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:29.16,0:10:35.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,F-Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.33,0:10:43.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They shot him...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.84,0:10:53.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.24,0:11:08.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.61,0:11:15.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tranquillizer bullets, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.91,0:11:20.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You damn fishman with superhuman\Nstrength! That serves you right!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:20.33,0:11:22.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san! Why'd you do that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:22.55,0:11:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, guys! What're you doing?!\NHurry up and capture them!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.09,0:11:31.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll take everyone from the ferocious\NTom's Workers company to Enies Lobby!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.35,0:11:33.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that Tom is such a dangerous person...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.76,0:11:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell is he thinking?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.77,0:11:40.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He really sold his soul to pirates!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.60,0:11:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He made that many battleships and\Nwaited for an opportunity like this!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.36,0:11:46.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You bastards! How dare you\Ntalk like that to Tom-san?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:46.65,0:11:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.86,0:11:50.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all right.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.24,0:11:51.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.57,0:11:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Judge...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.58,0:11:54.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.66,0:11:57.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll confess to the charge of\Nmaking a raid on the Judicial Ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.96,0:11:59.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.04,0:12:01.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! Tom-san! Don't!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.50,0:12:03.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I have a favor to ask.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.59,0:12:05.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up, you stupid fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.50,0:12:06.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who'd listen to a criminal's...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.96,0:12:08.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep your mouth shut, CP5!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.63,0:12:10.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.22,0:12:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So, what is the favor?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:11.97,0:12:17.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I can get one charge eliminated\Nfor our building the sea train...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.93,0:12:19.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...I'd like today's charge to be eliminated.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.98,0:12:21.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.10,0:12:26.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if that wish is granted,\Nyou'll just go back to square one.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.23,0:12:29.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You'll end up with the crime of building\Na ship for the King of the Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.32,0:12:31.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,which will result in the maximum penalty.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.41,0:12:34.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, I prefer that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.70,0:12:38.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,About assisting that Roger guy...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.20,0:12:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm resolutely proud of it!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.38,0:12:45.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How selfish...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.25,0:12:48.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,To think that he's proud of\Nassisting the King of the Pirates...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.59,0:12:49.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Traitor!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.59,0:12:52.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Ferocious fishman!\N--Damn fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.26,0:12:54.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san... Why?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.72,0:12:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.76,0:13:00.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Listen. Don't blame yourself, okay?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:00.52,0:13:05.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought that the Government\Nwould use force to get the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:05.36,0:13:08.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was at a bit of a disadvantage\Ndue to the matter with Roger.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.98,0:13:10.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But even so, you didn't have to--
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.86,0:13:12.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't worry.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.82,0:13:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at the town. Even if my charge\Ngoes back to what it was 14 years ago,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.41,0:13:18.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,everything is different from then.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.66,0:13:23.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This island is full of energy now.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.21,0:13:25.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is just the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.58,0:13:28.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No matter what happens to me,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.59,0:13:32.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can be of help to the town.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.05,0:13:34.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My dream has...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.01,0:13:40.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...finally... begun to run.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:40.64,0:13:43.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:43.98,0:13:50.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:50.40,0:13:53.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Iceberg... Franky...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:53.74,0:13:56.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take care of the blueprints.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:56.82,0:14:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro-san... Yokozuna...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.08,0:14:07.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thanks for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.29,0:14:09.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The tranquilizers have finally started working!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:09.21,0:14:11.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Capture those three culprits\Nfor the Judicial Ship raid!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.92,0:14:14.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, sir!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.26,0:14:15.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hold it!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.30,0:14:18.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Huh?\N--I'm changing the charges.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.01,0:14:23.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For the charge of building the pirate ship\Nfor Gold Roger, King of the Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.48,0:14:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we'll take shipbuilding\Nengineer Tom to Enies Lobby.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.61,0:14:32.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That is all.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.11,0:14:35.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What got into that old geezer?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:35.36,0:14:37.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well. I don't have\Nbusiness with his disciples.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.78,0:14:45.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Release those two disciples!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.25,0:14:49.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san can no longer be saved.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.38,0:14:53.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it's the World Government we're\Nup against, there's nothing we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.42,0:14:58.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bear it. Tom-san saved you two!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.18,0:14:59.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you make an enemy of them,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.97,0:15:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,no matter how many lives\Nyou have, it's not enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.43,0:15:06.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Enies Lobby is the judicial island\Nowned by the Government.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.77,0:15:08.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No criminals taken there...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:08.81,0:15:13.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...have ever returned!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.48,0:15:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The sea train is ready! We can take him now!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.28,0:15:18.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:18.61,0:15:21.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Kokoro-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.08,0:15:23.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you guys! Hurry up and take away...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:23.99,0:15:26.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.12,0:15:29.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this heavy, crazy fishman!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.96,0:15:31.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't do that!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.92,0:15:34.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.17,0:15:41.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.76,0:15:49.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:49.77,0:15:52.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Spandam-san's face got bent!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.02,0:15:55.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This time, Tom's disciple\Nstarted going on a rampage!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.61,0:15:57.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Stop it!\N--Ribbit, ribbit!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.24,0:16:01.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Capture him! The rest of you, take Tom away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:01.53,0:16:05.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fine by me! I won't let you take him away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:05.41,0:16:07.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You're allowed to shoot him!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.79,0:16:13.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give us Tom-san back!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.29,0:16:16.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you okay?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.84,0:16:18.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hurry up and run!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.55,0:16:26.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Fire!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.60,0:16:33.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! He got away!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.06,0:16:36.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll never let that Cutty Flam\Nbrat get away with this!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.98,0:16:39.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He is truly a criminal!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.53,0:16:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Once this case is over,\NI'll have him sent to the gallows!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.66,0:16:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Spandam-san!\N--What do you want?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.41,0:16:47.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I-It's Cutty Flam!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.00,0:16:49.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.54,0:16:51.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He came this far after us!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.08,0:16:58.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He's standing on the railway with some weapon!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.88,0:17:00.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stay there, Yokozuna.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.01,0:17:02.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.89,0:17:04.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is he stupid or what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.68,0:17:06.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What should we do?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.76,0:17:07.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you stupid, too?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.93,0:17:13.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just keep going; give him what he wants.\NDon't be concerned about him!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.15,0:17:17.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Y-Yes, sir.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.11,0:17:21.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop, Puffing Tom!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.95,0:17:29.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where are you taking your creator to?!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.09,0:17:40.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ribbit, ribbit...!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.21,0:17:47.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't let you pass here!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.22,0:17:51.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give Tom-san back to us!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.56,0:17:58.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Stop! Sea train!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.94,0:18:01.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see. Your parents abandoned you, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.99,0:18:04.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's so funny!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.03,0:18:05.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, you're laughing too hard!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.32,0:18:08.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, then! Come resolutely to my place!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.58,0:18:10.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.74,0:18:14.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't wanna build ships anymore!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.79,0:18:20.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't love ships that hurt\Nthe people I really care about!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.50,0:18:22.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But, Tom-san...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.97,0:18:30.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you're my goal after all!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.89,0:18:43.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So I want you to come back\Nand teach me again...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.49,0:18:50.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because I want to...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.87,0:18:56.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...build a dream ship someday, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:56.79,0:19:00.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A ship that resolutely and proudly traverses
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.42,0:19:03.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,even uncharted waves at edges of the earth!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:03.34,0:19:11.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A dream ship like that!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.15,0:19:25.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What we heard about Tom\Nis that he had good skills,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.15,0:19:28.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was a ferocious and intractable\Nfishman with superhuman strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.66,0:19:32.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Even if we ask the townspeople,\Nthey just speak ambiguously.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.45,0:19:37.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It must be tough to be a disciple that has\Nto defend such a man, huh, Cutty Flam?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.87,0:19:40.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's not even worth responding to.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.38,0:19:43.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You Government people are all crap!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.50,0:19:44.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?! Hey, hey...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.80,0:19:48.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,At that time, more than 100 people,\Nincluding marines and officials,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.01,0:19:52.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,were severely injured here in Water Seven.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.05,0:19:54.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit behind it was you.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.22,0:19:58.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You had a lot to answer for, causing the\NWorld Government that much trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.19,0:20:03.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but since you were confirmed dead in\Nthe sea train accident on that very day,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:03.02,0:20:05.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,your charge was annulled.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.53,0:20:10.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, we'll take you to\NEnies Lobby as a criminal.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.49,0:20:14.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can take your time there\Nanswering my question...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.74,0:20:20.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...about the whereabouts\Nof the blueprints for Pluton.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.42,0:20:28.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Blueno.\N--Yeah. It just connected.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.22,0:20:33.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When I reported this case to our chief,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.47,0:20:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he said he wanted to talk\Nto you right away, so...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.06,0:20:40.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your chief? Hm?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.27,0:20:41.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please go ahead, Chief.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.94,0:20:44.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ouch! It's hot! It's hot! It's hot!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.48,0:20:46.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I spilled the coffee!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.69,0:20:50.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dammit! Stupid coffee!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.45,0:20:52.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:52.24,0:20:53.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you there...
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.99,0:20:56.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...Cutty Flam?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.83,0:21:00.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Hm?\N--It's been a while.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.08,0:21:04.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I never thought you'd survived that...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.54,0:21:08.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's hard to believe, but I'm happy to hear it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.01,0:21:11.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who the hell are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.97,0:21:15.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,During these past eight years...\Nevery time my scars hurt,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.22,0:21:21.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was tormented by an anger that\NI couldn't take out on anyone...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.31,0:21:25.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...because the culprit who hurt me died!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.77,0:21:30.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll ask you again! Who the hell are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.24,0:21:36.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don't remember me?
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.12,0:21:40.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm the man who was from Cipher Pol No. 5
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.33,0:21:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and arrested Tom's Workers red-handed for\Nattacking the Judicial Ship eight years ago!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.74,0:22:19.22,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,We had a dream that day
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.24,0:22:24.06,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,Our belief in ourselves
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.08,0:22:32.08,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,makes us able to cross the wildly surging ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.30,0:22:41.30,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,You're braver and more caring than anyone else
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.85,0:22:50.85,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,If you ever depart this ship\Nand live in a different world
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.86,0:23:00.86,Italics,,0000,0000,0000,,In the end, we can all surely smile
Dialogue: 0,0:23:12.30,0:23:15.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've been eagerly looking forward to seeing you.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.09,0:23:16.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't tell me... Is that you, Spanda?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:16.63,0:23:18.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"M"! You're missing the "M"! It's "Spandam"!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.68,0:23:22.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Now, Lucci! Hurry up and bring\Nthem to Enies Lobby already!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.43,0:23:25.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--Roger.\N--Hey, hold it! Let him go!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.02,0:23:27.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,--What'd you say?\N--Oh, I'm sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.02,0:23:28.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.23,0:23:31.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Truth Behind Her Betrayal!\NRobin's Sorrowful Decision!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.31,0:23:39.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
